    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The orchestrator pattern extends the supervisor by adding dynamic task decomposition: rather than routing to a fixed set of named workers, the orchestrator first plans a list of sub-tasks and then spawns workers to execute them. The set of workers is determined at runtime based on the task, not hardcoded at graph-build time. This makes the orchestrator suitable for open-ended problems where the shape of work is unknown in advance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Orchestrator pattern: orchestrator decomposes task into plan, dynamically creates workers A-N in parallel, synthesizes results"
        }
      },
